"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an undirected tree rooted at node `0`, with `n` nodes numbered from 0 to `n - 1`. The tree is represented by a 2D integer array `edges` of length `n - 1`, where `edges[i] = [ui, vi]` indicates an edge between nodes `ui` and `vi`.\n\nYou are also given an integer array `nums` of length `n`, where `nums[i]` represents the value at node `i`, and an integer `k`.\n\nYou may perform **inversion operations** on a subset of nodes subject to the following rules:\n\n-\n\n**Subtree Inversion Operation:**\n\n-\n\nWhen you invert a node, every value in the [subtree](leetcode-keyword) rooted at that node is multiplied by -1.\n\n-\n\n**Distance Constraint on Inversions:**\n\n-\n\nYou may only invert a node if it is \"sufficiently far\" from any other inverted node.\n\n-\n\nSpecifically, if you invert two nodes `a` and `b` such that one is an ancestor of the other (i.e., if `LCA(a, b) = a` or `LCA(a, b) = b`), then the distance (the number of edges on the unique path between them) must be at least `k`.\n\nReturn the **maximum** possible **sum** of the tree's node values after applying **inversion operations**.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** edges = [[0,1],[0,2],[1,3],[1,4],[2,5],[2,6]], nums = [4,-8,-6,3,7,-2,5], k = 2\n\n**Output:** 27\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/3544-subtree-inversion-sum/3544-tree1-3.jpg","sequence":1,"sha256":"0e73bb677548b97d74e6e51c5f9b8566b2309d4b38de0aac0ed31cda742accb3","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"- Apply inversion operations at nodes 0, 3, 4 and 6.\n\n- The final `nums` array is `[-4, 8, 6, 3, 7, 2, 5]`, and the total sum is 27.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** edges = [[0,1],[1,2],[2,3],[3,4]], nums = [-1,3,-2,4,-5], k = 2\n\n**Output:** 9\n\n**Explanation:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/35