":3573,"problemSlug":"best-time-to-buy-and-sell-stock-v","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":3573,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Math","Enumeration","Number Theory"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given an array of positive integers `nums` and an integer `k`.\n\nYou may perform at most `k` operations. In each operation, you can choose one element in the array and **double** its value. Each element can be doubled **at most** once.\n\nThe **score** of a contiguous **[subarray](leetcode-keyword)** is defined as the **product** of its length and the *greatest common divisor (GCD)* of all its elements.\n\nYour task is to return the **maximum** **score** that can be achieved by selecting a contiguous subarray from the modified array.\n\n**Note:**\n\n- The **greatest common divisor (GCD)** of an array is the largest integer that evenly divides all the array elements.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [2,4], k = 1\n\n**Output:** 8\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Double `nums[0]` to 4 using one operation. The modified array becomes `[4, 4]`.\n\n- The GCD of the subarray `[4, 4]` is 4, and the length is 2.\n\n- Thus, the maximum possible score is `2 × 4 = 8`.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [3,5,7], k = 2\n\n**Output:** 14\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- Double `nums[2]` to 14 using one operation. The modified array becomes `[3, 5, 14]`.\n\n- The GCD of the subarray `[14]` is 14, and the length is 1.\n\n- Thus, the maximum possible score is `1 × 14 = 14`.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\n**Input:** nums = [5,5,5], k = 1\n\n**Output:** 15\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n- The subarray `[5, 5, 5]` has a GCD of 5, and its length is 3.\n\n- Since doubling any element doesn't improve the score, the maximum score is `3 × 5 = 15`.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= n == nums.length <= 1500`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 10⁹`\n\n- `1 <= k <= n`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Math","Enumera